# Lean Canvas

A one-page business model to test core startup hypotheses quickly.
Map problem, solution, metrics, and unfair advantages.

## Config
flow = TB
spacing = 70

## Problem
- [prob] Developers waste hours wiring up auth, billing, and boilerplate {hypothesis} {icon:💡}
  Top 3 problems our target customers face.
- [alt] Existing Alternatives: Roll-it-yourself, SaaS boilerplates, agency build {assumption}

## Customer Segments
- [seg] Indie SaaS founders building first product {icon:👤}
  Early adopters: solo devs with €1-5k/mo ARR target.
- [seg2] Early-stage startups (2-5 engineers) {icon:👥}

## Unique Value Proposition
- [uvp] Ship production-ready SaaS in a weekend {icon:⭐} {glow}
  Not a framework — a complete, opinionated starter kit.

## Solution
- [sol] Auth, billing, email, admin in one repo {done} {icon:✅}
- [sol2] One-command deploy to Fly/Railway {wip} {icon:⚡}
- [sol3] Lifetime license, no recurring fee {icon:💰}

## Channels
- [ch1] Twitter/X developer community {icon:🐦}
- [ch2] Hacker News Show HN {icon:📣}
- [ch3] Developer newsletters {icon:📰}

## Revenue Streams
- [rev] One-time license $199–$499 {icon:💵}
- [rev2] Premium support tier $99/mo {icon:🔧}

## Cost Structure
- [cost] Hosting demo env $50/mo {icon:🖥️}
- [cost2] Content & SEO $500/mo {icon:📝}

## Key Metrics
- [kpi] Monthly licenses sold {icon:📊}
- [kpi2] Time-to-first-deploy (target: <30 min) {icon:⏱️}
- [kpi3] Refund rate (target: <5%) {icon:📉}

## Unfair Advantage
- [adv] Deep SaaS ops experience (10+ yrs) {icon:🔒}

## Flow
prob --> uvp: drives
seg --> uvp: for
uvp --> sol: delivered via
sol --> rev: generates
ch1 --> seg: acquires
ch2 --> seg: acquires
kpi --> rev: measures
adv --> uvp: protects
